{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":18943,"record_hash":"sha256:b671af507b7e723028775e490399dbf0ca75305adf5d7e9b44cc330dad4452f9","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:21:37.865Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:321](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:321) `codex_capture_writes_metadata_and_is_idempotent` is doing too much: idempotency, GitMeta key layout, source indexing, Codex extraction, redaction, and stored JSON shape. Narrow it to idempotency plus stable shareable keys: first capture count, second capture `0`, transcript length unchanged, and maybe `gitbutler:agent-sessions` / `gitbutler:agent-session:*:transcript` existence. The `source_key`, exact `sources` set, `record_index`, and absent `agent`/`turn_id` assertions are brittle schema mirrors unless those fields are an explicit consumer contract.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:282](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:282) `capture_writes_claude_metadata_and_transcript` mostly repeats parser and redaction coverage from [transcript.rs:288](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:288) and [redaction.rs:209](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs:209). Keep only the Claude integration value: one stored record has the shared transcript shape after capture, and model/provider metadata lands in GitMeta. Drop the `sessionId` / `gitBranch` negative string checks here.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:378](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:378) `transcript_records_redact_secrets_and_copied_scalar_fields` is worth keeping as a boundary test, but should be narrower. Redaction algorithms are already covered in `redaction.rs`; this test only needs to prove GitMeta applies redaction to both copied scalar fields and `source_record`. Parse the stored JSON and assert a single sentinel secret is absent from `content_text` and `source_record`; delete the extra UUID/session-id coverage.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:423](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:423) `duplicate_recor\n[TRUNCATED]\non}` buckets. This matches `gitmeta-data-model.md`, but for the stated handoff/sharing paths the transcript already carries redacted `source_record`, and timeline rendering mainly needs per-record `role`, `content_text`, `tool_name`, and `event_kind`. I would not remove it now because it is documented and small, but it is the one shape that feels most like premature source-level bucketing.\\n\\n- Defer: [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:109) stores `record_index` in every transcript record. The GitMeta list order already provides timeline order, so this is not clearly required for session handoff or colleague sharing. Still, it is in the data model and useful as cheap provenance back to the original JSONL line, so I would leave it unless the model is being trimmed.\\n\\n**Should Clearly Stay**\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:65): `gitbutler:agent-sessions` should stay. It is the project-level entry point both docs describe.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:100): the single durable `:transcript` list should stay. It avoids branch/PR ownership guesses and keeps future relationship keys as references.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:89): `source_key` on each record should stay if multiple captured sources can merge into one durable session.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/